Paper: hep-th/0208162

Date: 2002-08-22

Title: On uncertainty relations in noncommutative quantum mechanics

Authors: Katarzyna Bolonek, Piotr Kosinski

Comments: 8 pages, revised version, few references added

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B547 (2002) 51-54

We discuss the uncertainty relations in quantum mechanics on noncommutativeplane. In particular, we show that, for a given state at most one out of threebasic nontrivial uncertainty relations can be saturated. We consider also insome detail the case of angular momentum eigenstates.